                                                <p><hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE.&#8212;<name type="person">Private Thomas Haley</name>, <name type="organization">Co. D, 91st New
                                                                York Volunteers</name>, aged 28 years, was wounded at
                                                                <name type="BATTLE" key="254">Petersburg, Virginia</name>, <date type="injury" when="1865-03-29">March 29th, 1865</date>, by a piece
                                                  of shell, which fractured the frontal bone just
                                                  above the right eye, causing hernia cerebri. He
                                                  was admitted to the <name type="hospital">hospital of the 1st division,
                                                                  Fifth Corps</name>, on <date type="admit" when="1865-04-02">April 2d</date>; sent to <name type="place">City Point</name>,
                                                  and thence conveyed to Washing ton and admitted to
                                                  the <name type="hospital">Armory Square Hospital</name> on <date type="transfer" when="1865-04-10">April 10th, 1865</date>.
                                                  Simple dressings were applied to the wound. On
                                                                <date type="operation" when="1865-04-27">April 27th</date>, a piece of the orbital bone which had
                                                  become loose was removed, otherwise the case
                                                  progressed well, and on <date type="hospitaldischarge" when="1865-07-18">July 18th, 1865</date>, Haley was
                                                                transferred to <name type="place">New York</name> for muster out. He is not
                                                  a pensioner.</p>
                                                
